===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|ic}}. The character does not appear as an independent character in the oracle bone script but appears as a component of {{zh-l|*𢓚}} and {{zh-l|*秜}}. The character shows a man ({{zh-l|*尸}}) sitting on or leaning on another man ({{zh-l|*匕}}), giving the original meaning of “to stop” or “close; intimate”; the derivative {{zh-l|*昵}} refers to the latter meaning.

Shuowen Jiezi considered it as a phono-semantic compound, but this is widely discredited by later scholars.

Compare [[化]], [[比]], [[北]], and [[卬]].

